androidx.media

Class MediaMetadata2.Builder

  • java.lang.Object
    • androidx.media.MediaMetadata2.Builder
  • Enclosing class:
    MediaMetadata2

    public static final class MediaMetadata2.Builder
extends java.lang.Object
    Use to build MediaMetadata2x objects. The system defined metadata keys must use the appropriate data type.

    • Constructor Summary

    • Constructor Detail

      • Builder

        public Builder()
        Create an empty Builder. Any field that should be included in the MediaMetadata2 must be added.

      • Builder

        public Builder(@NonNull
               MediaMetadata2 source)
        Create a Builder using a MediaMetadata2 instance to set the initial values. All fields in the source metadata will be included in the new metadata. Fields can be overwritten by adding the same key.
        Parameters:
        source -

      • Builder

        public Builder(MediaMetadata2 source,
               int maxBitmapSize)
        Create a Builder using a MediaMetadata2 instance to set initial values, but replace bitmaps with a scaled down copy if they are larger than maxBitmapSize.
        Parameters:
        source - The original metadata to copy.
        maxBitmapSize - The maximum height/width for bitmaps contained in the metadata.

      • putBitmap

        @NonNull
public MediaMetadata2.Builder putBitmap(@NonNull
                                                 java.lang.String key,
                                                 @Nullable
                                                 Bitmap value)
        Put a Bitmap into the metadata. Custom keys may be used, but if the METADATA_KEYs defined in this class are used they may only be one of the following:
        • MediaMetadata2.METADATA_KEY_ART
        • MediaMetadata2.METADATA_KEY_ALBUM_ART
        • MediaMetadata2.METADATA_KEY_DISPLAY_ICON
        Large bitmaps may be scaled down by the system when android.media.session.MediaSession#setMetadata is called. To pass full resolution images Uris should be used with putString(java.lang.String, java.lang.String).
        Parameters:
        key - The key for referencing this value
        value - The Bitmap to store
        Returns:
        The Builder to allow chaining

Generated javadoc for the new package structure to make it clearer which packages are bundled with the Android operating system, and which are packaged with your app's APK. Going forward, the android.* package hierarchy will be reserved for Android packages that ship with the operating system; other packages will be issued in the new androidx.* package hiearchy.
